document_data.Description:
{{Quote|Sez here that 'goblinoids are obstreperous and malodorous...|Booyagh [[Piddle]], reading from ''[[On Goblins: My Life Among the Conquering Host]].''}}

Goblins usually stood between {{SIrange|3'4"|3'8"|ft-in}} and weighed about {{SIrange|40|55|lbs|k}} on average. They had flat faces, sloped back forehead, broad noses, pointed ears, and small, sharp fangs. and their eyes varied in color from red to yellow. Their skin color ranged from yellow through any shade of orange to a deep red, though they also came in shades of green. All members of the same tribe normally shared the same skin color 

Goblins typically dressed in dark [[leather armor|leathers]] soiled by poor hygiene and colored in a similar range of tones to their skin.
